title: Fortios: BGP Peer
agents: special
catalog: network/fortigate
license: GPLv2
distribution: check_mk
description:
 This check monitors the BGP peers of a Fortigate firewall.
 It changes the status to {crit} if the respective BGP peer 
 status is not set to “Established”.
 The check shows the local IP of the peer, 
 the remote AS and the remote IP of the peer.


 The special agent is required for this check, 
 which can be configured via “FortiOS”.

discovery:
 One service per bgp peer is created.